Evidence: Notably, the addition of GABA into the cell culture medium promoted the proliferation of GABRQ expressing HepG2 cells, but not GABRQ-knockdown HepG2 cells, which means that GABA stimulates HepG2 cell growth through GABRQ.
Subject: a(PUBCHEM:119)

Evidence: Knockdown of endogenous GABRQ expression in HepG2 attenuated HCC cell growth, suggesting its role in HCC cell viability.
Subject: p(HGNC:GABRQ)
